The Global Packaging Market was valued at USD 970.7 Bn in 2020 and is expected to reach USD 1240.5 Bn by 2027, growing at a CAGR of 3.6% during the forecast period. The market will benefit from rising real incomes, rapid growth in e-commerce, rising urbanization and the development of retail industry in the developing and emerging countries of Asia, Middle East & Africa. The packaging consumption in these regions is projected to grow faster than in other regions by 2024. Asia Pacific accounted for 40% of the global packaging consumption in 2020, followed by North America with 22% of the market share.

The green packaging segment was a significant contributor to the market in 2020 and is estimated to reach USD 342 Bn by 2027 at a CAGR of 7%. Major players such as Amazon, Google, Tetrapak, etc are increasingly adopting green packaging to achieve net-zero carbon footprint. This is expected to create immense opportunities for the green packaging market.

